<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/114a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-05T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5959. For <persName corresp="#p_CB1">Colby</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_MFC1">Munson</persName>:</p>
                            <p>Your cable 1st. See ours <persName corresp="#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> about Denmark.<note n="1" xml:id="d543fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_635">p.
                                    635</ref>.</note> As regards Norwegian tonnage as soon as
                                proposed basis of understanding was reached all Norwegian tonnage
                                was released. Cable with full basis was forwarded by British Embassy
                                on November 25. No reply confirming arrangement has yet been
                                received. In the meantime England making every effort to divert
                                Norwegian tonnage to the other side in order to keep under their
                                control. This reduces amount that will be under our control. We urge
                                confirmation agreement by Great Britain without delay.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>